.TH "snd_hda_codec_set_pin_target" 9 "snd_hda_codec_set_pin_target" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_codec_set_pin_target \- remember the current pinctl target value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_codec_set_pin_target
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "unsigned int val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "nid" 12
pin NID
.IP "val" 12
assigned pinctl value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function stores the given value to a pinctl target value in the
pincfg table.  This isn't always as same as the actually written value
but can be referred at any time via \fBsnd_hda_codec_get_pin_target\fP.
